ğŸ”¹ Polymorphism â€“ Interview Answer

Polymorphism is an OOPS concept where one method or object can take multiple forms.
It allows the same method name to behave differently based on the object or situation.

ğŸ”¹ Real-Life Example

A simple example is the word â€œdrive.â€
Driving a car and driving a bike use the same action but work differently.

ğŸ”¹ Types of Polymorphism

There are two types of polymorphism:

Compile-time polymorphism, achieved using method overloading

Run-time polymorphism, achieved using method overriding

ğŸ”¹ Java Perspective

In Java, compile-time polymorphism is achieved through method overloading, and run-time polymorphism is achieved through method overriding with inheritance.

ğŸ”¹ One-Line Closing

Polymorphism makes code flexible, reusable, and easy to extend.